## PR Description

When reviewing this method, I noticed that the validator index check has a bug. It should return an error when validator index is equal to `getValidators().size()`. Assuming `SszList` is zero-indexed, which I'm pretty sure it is, that entry won't exist. I would have included a test, but since it's not a static method it's not that straight-forward.

Simple external example:

```java
int index = 3;
List<Integer> list = List.of(1, 2, 3);
if (list.size() < index) {
    System.out.println("invalid index");
} else {
    System.out.println("valid index");
    System.out.println(list.get(index));
}
```

```
